centrust didn't meet the deadline. 

the collection was at the heart of a grandiose plan mr. paul had in which the art was to do double duty -- as an investment for centrust and as decoration for the s&l's new office tower, designed by i.m. pei.
the rub is that the $28 million was plucked from the funds of this federally insured institution even as centrust was losing money hand over fist.
mr. paul had no right to buy art for the s&l in the first place -- it isn't on the comptroller's "permissible" list -- without seeking a special dispensation, which he did not do.
